.SH "NAME"
env \- environment variable file format
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fB.env\fP files contain environment variable definitions in key\-value format.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The dotenv file format provides a simple method for defining environment
variables in plain text files. These files typically use the \fB.env\fP extension
and contain variable definitions that can be loaded into the environment of
applications or processes.
.SH "FILE FORMAT"
.SS "Basic Syntax"
.sp
The basic syntax consists of key\-value pairs separated by an equals sign:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
KEY=value
ANOTHER_KEY=another value
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SS "Key Naming Rules"
.sp
Variable names must follow these conventions:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Must start with a letter (a\-z, A\-Z) or underscore (_)
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Can contain letters, digits (0\-9), and underscores
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Case sensitive (typically uppercase by convention)
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Cannot contain spaces or special characters except underscore
.RE
.sp
Valid examples:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
DATABASE_URL=example
_PRIVATE_KEY=secret
API_VERSION_2=v2.1
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SH "QUOTING BEHAVIOR"
.sp
The dotenv format supports three quoting modes with distinct behaviors:
.SS "Unquoted Values (Literal)"
.sp
Unquoted values are treated literally with leading and trailing whitespace
trimmed:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
NAME=John Doe
PATH=/usr/local/bin
DEBUG=true
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Special characters, escape sequences, and variable references are treated as
literal text.
.SS "Single\-Quoted Values (Literal with Minimal Escaping)"
.sp
Single\-quoted values preserve all characters literally. The only supported
escape sequence is \fB\(rs\*(Aq\fP for including a literal single quote:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
MESSAGE=\*(AqHello World\*(Aq
PATH_WITH_SPACES=\*(Aq\&  /path/with spaces\&  \*(Aq
LITERAL_BACKSLASHES=\*(AqC:\(rsWindows\(rsSystem32\*(Aq
QUOTE_EXAMPLE=\*(AqIt\*(Aq\(rs\*(Aq\*(Aqs a beautiful day\*(Aq
JSON_CONFIG=\*(Aq{"key": "value", "number": 42}\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Within single quotes:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Backslashes are literal (no escape processing)
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Variable substitution is disabled
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Newlines and special characters are preserved
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Only \(rs\*(Aq is interpreted as an escaped single quote
.RE
.SS "Double\-Quoted Values (Full Processing)"
.sp
Double\-quoted values support full escape sequence processing and variable
substitution:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
MESSAGE="Hello \(rs"World\(rs""
MULTILINE="Line 1\(rsnLine 2\(rsnLine 3"
PATH="C:\(rs\(rsWindows\(rs\(rsSystem32"
GREETING="Hello $USER, welcome!"
CONFIG_PATH="${HOME}/.config/myapp"
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
\fBSupported escape sequences:\fP
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\(rs" \- literal double quote
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\(rs\(rs \- literal backslash
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\(rsn \- newline character
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\(rst \- tab character
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\(rsr \- carriage return
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\(rsf \- form feed
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\(rsb \- backspace
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
\(rsv \- vertical tab
.RE
.SH "MULTILINE VALUES"
.sp
Multiline values are supported only within quoted strings (single or double
quotes):
.SS "Single\-Quoted Multiline"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
PRIVATE_KEY=\*(Aq\-\-\-\-\-BEGIN PRIVATE KEY\-\-\-\-\-
MIIEvQIBADANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAASCBKcwggSjAgEAAoIBAQC7
VGhT7sMV0f7KfFQk8vX9YgH2pL9eN3mK1jR5wS8uA7B6cD9fE0
\-\-\-\-\-END PRIVATE KEY\-\-\-\-\-\*(Aq
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SS "Double\-Quoted Multiline"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
SQL_QUERY="SELECT users.id, users.name, profiles.bio
FROM users
INNER JOIN profiles ON users.id = profiles.user_id
WHERE users.active = true"
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SH "VARIABLE SUBSTITUTION"
.sp
Variable substitution is performed only within double\-quoted values. Three
forms are supported:
.SS "Basic Substitution ($VAR)"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
HOME=/home/user
CONFIG_PATH="$HOME/.config"
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SS "Explicit Boundaries (${VAR})"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
PREFIX=app
LOGFILE="${PREFIX}_error.log"
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SS "Default Values (${VAR:\-default})"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
DATABASE_HOST="${DB_HOST:\-localhost}"
PORT="${SERVER_PORT:\-3000}"
DEBUG_MODE="${DEBUG:\-false}"
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
\fBSubstitution Rules:\fP
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Variables are resolved from the current environment
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
If a variable is undefined, $VAR and ${VAR} expand to empty string
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
${VAR:\-default} uses the default value if VAR is undefined or empty
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Nested substitution is not supported
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Substitution occurs only in double\-quoted contexts
.RE
.SH "COMMENTS"
.SS "Full\-Line Comments"
.sp
Lines beginning with # (optionally preceded by whitespace) are comments:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
# Application configuration
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://localhost:5432/mydb

    # Cache settings
REDIS_HOST=localhost
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SS "End\-of\-Line Comments"
.sp
Comments can appear at the end of variable definitions:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://localhost:5432/mydb\&  # Production database
DEBUG=false\&  # Disable debug mode in production
API_KEY=secret123\&  # TODO: rotate this key monthly
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
\fBComment Rules:\fP
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Comments extend from # to the end of the line
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
# characters within quoted strings are literal, not comment markers
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Leading whitespace before # is ignored for full\-line comments
.RE
.SH "BLANK LINES AND WHITESPACE"
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Blank lines and lines containing only whitespace are ignored
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Leading and trailing whitespace around keys and unquoted values is trimmed
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Whitespace within quoted values is preserved exactly
.RE
.SH "PROCESSING ORDER"
.sp
Variables are processed in the order they appear in the file:
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
BASE_URL=https://api.example.com
API_ENDPOINT="$BASE_URL/v1/users"\&  # References BASE_URL defined above
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.sp
Later definitions may reference earlier ones, but forward references are not
supported.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.SS "Basic Configuration"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
# Database settings
DATABASE_HOST=localhost
DATABASE_PORT=5432
DATABASE_NAME=myapp

# Application settings
DEBUG=true
LOG_LEVEL=info
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SS "Complex Configuration with Substitution"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
# Environment setup
ENV=production
APP_NAME=myservice

# Paths
HOME_DIR=/opt/myservice
CONFIG_DIR="${HOME_DIR}/config"
LOG_DIR="${HOME_DIR}/logs"

# Database configuration
DB_HOST="${DATABASE_HOST:\-localhost}"
DB_NAME="${APP_NAME}_${ENV}"
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://${DB_USER}:${DB_PASS}@${DB_HOST}:5432/${DB_NAME}"

# Multiline private key
PRIVATE_KEY="\-\-\-\-\-BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY\-\-\-\-\-
MIIEpAIBAAKCAQEA2Z9QJG8YgN7jkF1L3vX9YgH2pL9eN3mK1jR5
wS8uA7B6cD9fE0GhT7sMV0f7KfFQk8vX9YgH2pL9eN3mK1jR5wS
\-\-\-\-\-END RSA PRIVATE KEY\-\-\-\-\-"
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SS "Quoting Examples"
.sp
.if n .RS 4
.nf
.fam C
# Unquoted \- spaces trimmed
MESSAGE=Hello World

# Single quoted \- literal preservation
JSON_DATA=\*(Aq{"status": "ok", "count": 42}\*(Aq
WINDOWS_PATH=\*(AqC:\(rsProgram Files\(rsMyApp\*(Aq

# Double quoted \- full processing
FORMATTED_MESSAGE="Welcome ${USER}!\(rsnToday is $(date)"
ESCAPED_QUOTES="He said \(rs"Hello\(rs" to me"
.fam
.fi
.if n .RE
.SH "COMPATIBILITY NOTES"
.sp
This specification defines a standard dotenv format. Individual implementations
may vary in:
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Support for additional escape sequences
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Handling of malformed syntax
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Variable resolution precedence
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.  sp -1
.  IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
Maximum line length limits
.RE
.sp
Applications should document any deviations from this standard format.
